text: Wakefield is a village in the town of South Kingstown, Rhode Island, and the commercial center of the town. The U.S. Census calls the village a component of the census-designated place. It was the traditional county seat of Washington County. Since 1991, the Washington County Courthouse has been in Wakefield. ==References== ==Other websites== *Town of South Kingstown, Rhode Island Category:County seats in Rhode Island
title: Wakefield, Rhode Island
